From: ROCm runtime/driver team <gpu-driver@amd.com>
Subject: [PATCH RFC v1] amdkfd: cgroup-aware unified pin budget (K-5)

Replace the static system-wide `dmabuf_pin_max_mb` cap with a
per-process effective cap derived from the calling process's memcg
memory.max. Enable the same primitive for host-pinned allocations
(hipHostMalloc).

Motivation
----------
V17.4.1 ships dmabuf_pin_max_mb=4096 as a single global cap. This is
too small for single-tenant inference pods (16+ GiB KV cache), too
large for shared multi-tenant test boxes, and the wrong shape for
mixed deployments. The orchestrator already encodes the right cap
per-pod via memory cgroups; this patch teaches the driver to read it.

Design
------
The per-process effective cap comes from one of two existing
authoritative signals (no new fallback constants):

  - in real cgroup (memcg.max < LONG_MAX):
        cap = memcg.max * dmabuf_pin_cgroup_ratio_pct / 100   (default 75)

  - root cgroup / unlimited / no CONFIG_MEMCG:
        cap = dmabuf_pin_max_mb * dmabuf_pin_default_ratio_pct / 100
                                                              (default 95)

The 5% headroom in the no-cgroup branch prevents a single process
from hitting the exact system ceiling and surprise-rejecting at the
+1 byte boundary. No floor, no ceiling, no fallback constant.

The cgroup branch is intentionally NOT clamped by dmabuf_pin_max_mb
so a 32 GiB cgroup pod automatically gets 24 GiB per-proc cap even
on the V17.4.1 default dmabuf_pin_max_mb=4096 host. Cumulative defense
across processes is the existing per-GPU adev->kfd.rdma_pinned_bytes
counter.

Test plan
---------
- mr_burn_dmabuf under 4/8/16/32/64 GiB cgroup limits — caps scale 75%
- multistream_combo 5-min run — no perf regression
- startup_stress with all V16-shim ENVs stripped — passes
- 4-pod simultaneous saturate — fairness preserved
- bare-metal no-cgroup case — cap = dmabuf_pin_max_mb x 95%

Revision history
----------------
v0 (2026-04-30): 5 module params (floor / ceiling / unlimited_default).
v1 (2026-05-01): dropped 3 fragile params; cap derives only from
                 memcg.max or dmabuf_pin_max_mb. The 0.95 headroom
                 replaces the unlimited_default constant.

Signed-off-by: ROCm runtime/driver team <gpu-driver@amd.com>
